    "instruction": "Diagnosis summary:\n\nRoot-cause component: ts-order-service\nFailure reason: high CPU usage / resource pressure leading to degraded latency and increased request counts (observed as elevated log.row_count and trace row_count). Evidence: cpu KPI for ts-order-service breached its global P95 earliest at 2024-02-24T23:19:00+00:00 with the largest relative deviation (~78% above P95) among candidate services; correlated increases in latency metrics and log.row_count/trace row_count in the same incident window; no error logs recorded. Recommended immediate actions: consider scaling ts-order-service (increase CPU/resource), throttle incoming traffic, and inspect recent deployments or traffic spikes around 23:19 UTC. If you want, I can instruct the Executor to produce the exact per-timestamp metric rows for ts-order-service cpu/latency and corresponding log.row_count entries during the window for a precise timeline."}

Final diagnosis: the incident was caused by ts-order-service experiencing high CPU usage, first observed at 2024-02-24 23:19:00 UTC.

